            "Adjacent divided by Hypotenuse"
          ]
        },
        {
          "questionText": "What are the two steps required to calculate the mean of a set of test results?",
          "answerGuidance": [
            "Add all values together",
            "Divide by the total count of readings",
            "Sum and divide"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "deeperQuestionText": "In an electrical impedance triangle, why must you identify the 90-degree angle before you can accurately use Pythagoras’ Theorem?",
      "deeperAnswerGuidance": [
        "The 90-degree angle identifies which side is the hypotenuse",
        "Pythagoras’ Theorem only applies to right-angled triangles",
        "The hypotenuse must be the side alone on one side of the equation (c²)",
        "Misidentifying the sides would lead to an incorrect calculation of the longest side"
      ],
      "hint": "The hypotenuse is always the longest side and is never the side forming the 90-degree corner."
    }
  ]
}

